  "prompt": "How can you tell who has viewed Instagram videos?",
  "response": "Instagram does not provide a feature that allows users to see who has viewed their regular posts, photos, or videos in the feed. However, there are some specific types of content on Instagram where you can see viewers:\n\n1. **Instagram Stories**: For Stories, you can see who has viewed them by swiping up on your active Story. A list of viewers will appear, showing the usernames of people who have watched your Story.\n\n2. **Instagram Live Videos**: If you go live on Instagram, you can see viewers in real-time. After the live session ends, you can also see the number of viewers and their usernames during the replay.\n\n3. **Instagram Reels**: For Reels, you can see the number of views (indicated by a count below the Reel), but Instagram does not provide a list of specific users who viewed your Reel.\n\nFor standard video posts in your feed, Instagram only shows the total number of likes, comments, and views, but not the identities of the viewers.\n\nIf you come across third-party apps or services claiming to show who viewed your Instagram videos, be cautious. These are often scams and may compromise your account security.",
